<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-aCUdvxLCIvRe3Wgu9xCtdA" name=",_unWt4KZKEeCmzNtTCfivQw" guid="-aCUdvxLCIvRe3Wgu9xCtdA" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    ISO 26262, volume 8, clause 9 defines the guidance for generic aspects of verification planning which should be&#xD;
    followed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In order to detect systematic faults within the implementation of system design during the hardware-software&#xD;
    integration various test methods must be selected that cover a variety of aspects of test and verification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The selection of the application&amp;nbsp;feasible methods are detailed in the step section.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>If the item is ASIL C or D then&amp;nbsp;it is required to plan&amp;nbsp;for the complete testing of the hardware software&#xD;
interface requirements at the HW-SW integration level. Otherwise a rationale will be provided that no remaining issue of&#xD;
the hardware software interface exists.</keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_1dAykKZUEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Select methods for the correctness of implementation of system design specification and technical safety requirements" guid="_1dAykKZUEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
